#1. Configuration


  ##1-1. Service Installation
  &lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open command prompt (as administrator)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;type: cd &amp;quot;C:\Windows\Microsoft.NET\Framework64\v4.0.30319&amp;quot; and press enter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Type: installutil &amp;quot;C:\actionframework\agents\33333\ActionFramework.Agent.exe&amp;quot; and press enter. Results should look like the image below.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src&#x3D;&quot;data:image/png;base64,&#x3D;&#x3D;&quot; alt&#x3D;&quot;Installation complete&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;li&gt;Open services in windows, if it does not show, press refresh button and the Agent should appear in the list like the image below.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src&#x3D;&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot; alt&#x3D;&quot;Agent added to Windows Services.&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;li&gt;Start agent service manually by pressing the &amp;quot;start&amp;quot; link-button.&lt;/li&gt;

#2. Actions


  ##2-1. Create an Action
  &lt;p&gt;Create an action class that inherits from ActionBase.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class&#x3D;&quot;language-csharp&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;
using ActionFramework.Base;
using System;

namespace DemoApp
{
    public class DemoAction1 : ActionBase
    {
        //define the runtime configuration properties
        public string MyProp { get; set; }

        //override the runtime &amp;amp;quot;execute&amp;amp;quot; function
        public override object Execute()
        {
            try
            {
                //implement action logic, log my &amp;amp;quot;MyProp&amp;amp;quot; value
                Log.Info(&amp;amp;quot;Just make a log entry: &amp;amp;quot; + MyProp);

                return HandleSuccess();
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {
                return HandleException(ex);
            }
        }
    }
}
&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;

  ##2-2. On Demand (REST) Actions
  &lt;p&gt;Build the Action class.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class&#x3D;&quot;language-csharp&quot;&gt;
&lt;code&gt;
public class OnDemandDemo : ActionBase
{
    //GET (no parameters)
        public override object Execute()
        {
            try
            {
                XDocument result &#x3D; XDocument.Parse(&amp;amp;quot;&amp;lt;xml&amp;gt;content&amp;lt;/xml&amp;gt;&amp;amp;quot;);

                Log.Info(&amp;amp;quot;Parsed filecontent successfully&amp;amp;quot;);

                return result;
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {
                return HandleException(ex);
            }
        }

        //POST (object input parameter)
        public override object Execute(object input)
        {
            try
            {
                Log.Info(&amp;amp;quot;Object Input: &amp;amp;quot; + input.ToString());

                return input;
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {
                return HandleException(ex);
            }
        }
}
&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Call the agent API endpoints (GET/POST).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class&#x3D;&quot;language-csharp&quot;&gt;
&lt;code&gt;
string uri &#x3D; &amp;amp;quot;http://localhost:1011/&amp;amp;quot;;

//GET:
var getclient &#x3D; new RestClient(uri);
var getrequest &#x3D; new RestRequest(&amp;amp;quot;api/agent/runaction/ondemanddemo&amp;amp;quot;, Method.GET);
var getresponse &#x3D; getclient.Execute(getrequest);
Console.WriteLine(getresponse.Content);
Console.ReadLine();

//POST:
var postclient &#x3D; new RestClient(uri);
var postrequest &#x3D; new RestRequest(&amp;amp;quot;api/agent/runaction?name&#x3D;ondemanddemo&amp;amp;quot;, Method.POST);
postrequest.RequestFormat &#x3D; DataFormat.Json;
postrequest.AddBody(new TestModel()
{
    Id &#x3D; 1,
    Name &#x3D; &amp;amp;quot;Test&amp;amp;quot;
});

var postresponse &#x3D; postclient.Execute(postrequest);
Console.WriteLine(postresponse.Content);
Console.ReadLine();
&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;

#3. Logging


  ##3-1. Create custom log class
  &lt;p&gt;Create a class that inherits from &lt;strong&gt;ILogElement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class&#x3D;&quot;language-csharp&quot;&gt;
&lt;code&gt;
using ActionFramework.Logging;
using System;

namespace DemoApp
{
    internal sealed class CustomLog : ILogElement
    {
        private int amount &#x3D; 0;
        private DateTime date &#x3D; DateTime.Now;

        public int Amount
        {
            get { return amount; }
        }

        public DateTime Date
        {
            get { return date; }
            set { date &#x3D; value; }
        }

        public string Message { get; set; }

        /// &amp;lt;summary&amp;gt;
        /// increase count by 1
        /// &amp;lt;/summary&amp;gt;
        public void Count()
        {
            amount++;
        }

        /// &amp;lt;summary&amp;gt;
        /// increase count by n
        /// &amp;lt;/summary&amp;gt;
        public void Count(int n)
        {
            amount +&#x3D; n;
        }
    }
}
&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Use the custom logging class in an action class.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class&#x3D;&quot;language-csharp&quot;&gt;
&lt;code&gt;
//create the custom log and add values
var log &#x3D; new CustomLog()
{
    Date &#x3D; DateTime.Now,
    Message &#x3D; &amp;amp;quot;This is the custom message&amp;amp;quot;
};

//add a count
log.Count(25);

//create the log
Log.Custom(log);
&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Log output (XML).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class&#x3D;&quot;language-markup&quot;&gt;

    &amp;lt;message&amp;gt;This is the custom message&amp;lt;/message&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/customlog&amp;gt;
&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;

#5. How to update documentation


  ##Document builder
  &lt;h2 id&#x3D;&quot;how-to-use-the-documentation-tool&quot;&gt;How to use the documentation tool&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Download code. Open terminal at project location. Install dependencies &lt;code&gt;npm install&lt;/code&gt;. Create folders in docs, or modify example contents. This is where you put your partial html or markdown files. Names of the document sections is derived from file- and folder names.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id&#x3D;&quot;custom-styles-and-scripts&quot;&gt;Custom styles and scripts&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Put js and css files in &amp;quot;scripts&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;styles&amp;quot; respectively to have them included inline in the output document.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id&#x3D;&quot;syntax-highlight&quot;&gt;Syntax highlight&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The project comes preconfigured with prismjs for c#, asp.net, javascript, css and markup. Add code blocks wrapped in applicable tags to partial html files to have them output highlighted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;&amp;amp;lt;pre class&#x3D;&amp;amp;quot;language-aspnet&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;code&amp;amp;gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h2 id&#x3D;&quot;assets-adding-images-&quot;&gt;Assets (adding images)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Put image files into &lt;code&gt;assets&lt;/code&gt; folder and link them relative to &lt;em&gt;root project path&lt;/em&gt;, like so: &lt;code&gt;&amp;amp;lt;img src&#x3D;&amp;amp;quot;assets/my-image.png&amp;amp;quot; /&amp;amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; Supported formats are .jpg, .gif, .png. Files are encoded into base64 and inserted inline.&lt;/p&gt;
